column8: The material has been arranged into four series – kBa’ ‘gyur, miscellaneous canonical material, rNying ma rGyud ‘bum and Rinpoche’s Private Library.
column9: Digital copies have been retained by Gangtey Monastery, and deposited with the National Library and Archives of Bhutan.
column10: Material in this collection was copied as part of the project: EAP039 Digital Documentation of the Manuscript Collection in Gangtey. RAW and JPEG images were made, and deposited with The British Library. Copies were also deposited with the National Library and Archives of Bhutan. The originals are held by Gangtey Monastery. Information used to create this catalogue was supplied by the Project.
column19: 5 hard drives containing 485 volumes, consisting of 135785 TIFF Images
column32: Original material is held by Gangtey Monastery.
column34: Digital documentation of manuscript collection in Gangtey
column37: This collection includes a set of the 100-volume bKa’ ’gyur, two sets of the 46-volume rNying ma rGyud ’bum, the world’s largest Astasahasrikaprajńaparamita, and about a hundred miscellaneous titles.Written in the dBu can script, the cursive dBu med script, the ‘Bru tsha script and the Khyug yig script.Originals dated as: c 14th-early 20th century.
column41: Access for research purposes only. Not to be reproduced without written permission from Gangtey Monastery.

column8: The material is arranged by titled volumes. An EAP Reference Number has been added.
